text: The first floor is mainly eateries while the higher floors are mostly occupied by the Cornerstone church. Otherwise, nothing much happening here.

The Odeon Katong is a beautiful apartment development that has many charms to it. There are various facilities that residents can enjoy while living in The Odeon Katong. Residents of The Odeon Katong would not have to travel far to get their basic necessities as everything is close within their reach. Residents can enjoy taking evening walks around the apartment as well. closest bus stops are located at Roxy Square, Katong Shop Centre, Amber Gardens, Parkway Parade and The Holy Family Church.

One of the oldest malls in Singapore, with varied shops, cafes, and TCM. Now home to the vibrant Cornerstone Community Church, which is worth a visit. A charming spot in a friendly neighborhood, full of life.
Was at the Cornerstone Church at 10.15 am. Nice place. There are 2 cafes on the ground floor. Had breakfast at The Whole kitchen.

I was at this Wan Mei dessert place hidden backlane of Katong Odeon East Coast Road. Tried the Red Tea Longans Ice on the warm evening is really nice! Price is reasonable just over SGD4,  serving reasonable not too sweet. Of course the fine ice is not as fluffy but small flaw. I will be back to try the rest.
